The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, March 7: The new wholesale price-based index for measuring inflation will be rolled out from May 14. The new index, with 2004-05 as the base year, will have 250 new items and is expected to provide a more realistic picture of the price rise. Items such as type writers and VCRs will be replaced with mobile phones and LCD television sets in the new index.                             
	 New Delhi, March 7: States have shown poor response to the Centres offer for extra allocation of wheat and rice for the public distribution system at higher than the subsidised price. States have lifted only 2.31 lakh tonnes from the 36.07 lakh tonnes of wheat and rice earmarked for the January-February period.                             
	 New Delhi, March 7: The EPFO is considering handing over its business to other banks, irked by the State Banks unilateral decision to raise charges on provident fund collections. The retirement fund manager has decided to start negotiations with other banks to explore the possibility of switching over the collection business, a labour ministry source said.                            
	 New Delhi, March 7: The mines ministry is likely to give an in-principle approval to Rio Tinto for its diamond mining project in Madhya Pradesh, in which the firm is looking to invest around Rs 2,200 crore.                            
	 New Delhi, March 7: The share of auto parts imported from China in the domestic market is expected to increase twelve-fold to touch $6.85 billion (over Rs 30,000 crore) by 2012-13, industry body Ficci said in a report.                                                                                                                          
